descriptions:
Role: A Business Development Manager must be dynamically driven to prospect, qualify and aid in lead generation. Developing lasting relationships with key decision makers of the client organization, a business development must help to push forth the brand trust with industry professionals globally.
Job responsibilities:
· Research Potential Client Organization, their Businesses and Contacts to find Opportunities for Collaboration;
· Generate leads through cold calling which should lead to Conversion (should have knowledge how to sell Software Product and Services in the area of Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning);
· Penetrate the Accounts, and Establish Excellent Relationships with CXOs, Technical/Engineering Leaders and other Key Stakeholders within Client Organization;
· Responsible for gathering RFPs, RFQs and develop Quotes and Proposals for Clients working closely with Engineering Leaders;
· Conduct product demonstrations encompassing both technical and non-technical aspects;
· Build long term association with new Clients and responsible for up selling and cross selling;
· Maintains relationships with customers by providing support, information, and guidance; researching and recommending new opportunities; recommending profit and service improvements;
· Identifies product improvements or new products by remaining current on industry trends, market activities, and competitors;
· Maintain the Healthy Sales Funnel and Pipeline as per defined Monthly, Quarterly and Annual Target;
· Prepares reports by collecting, analyzing, and summarizing information;
· Achieve and report on key KPIs agreed with the CEO.
Desired Skills:
· 7-10 years’ experience in a Business Development;
· Excellent research, planning and organisation skills;
· Demonstrated ability to convert prospects and close deals by phone and in person while maintaining established sales quotas;
· 5+ years proven track record of success in sales/business development in a target driven environment, ideally in CRM/Saas/High-Tech;
· Technology savvy and proficient in the use of a range of communication, presentation and other business tools;
· Proven track record of success in B2B sales, defense market;
· Excellent interpersonal skills and ability to communicate (oral and written) effectively;
· Strong work ethics;
· Passion for selling and enthusiastic self-starter with a can do attitude.
· Excellent problem solving skills and the zeal to learn quickly and adapt to changing requirements
· Ability to collaborate and work independently when required.
Ability to learn and apply new technologies quickly
Job Type: Full-time
Salary: ₹700,000.00 - ₹1,200,000.00 per year
Benefits:
Cell phone reimbursement
Leave encashment
Paid sick time
Paid time off
Provident Fund
Schedule:
Day shift
Fixed shift
Monday to Friday
Supplemental pay types:
Performance bonus
Experience:
B2B sales: 3 years (Preferred)
Ability to Commute:
Bangalore City, Karnataka (Preferred)
